#*: Though we are justices and doctors and churchmen {{...}} we have some '''salt''' of our youth in us.
# {{lb|en|obsolete}} [[piquancy|Piquancy]]; [[wit]]; [[sense]].
#: ''Attic '''salt'''''
# {{lb|en|obsolete}} A dish for salt at table; a [[salt cellar]].
#* Samuel Pepys
#*: I out and bought some things; among others, a dozen of silver '''salts'''.
# {{lb|en|figurative}} [[skepticism|Skepticism]] and [[common sense]].
#: ''Any politician's statements must be taken [[with a grain of salt|with a grain of '''salt''']], but his need to be taken with a whole shaker of '''salt'''.''
